{
  "_notes": "Configured from the live site (June 2026). BESTCA runs a newer SearchSpring \"Snap\" storefront theme + CAD pricing, unlike BESTUS. Quirks: category taxonomy is /any-surface-access-doors/... (no /products/ — it 404s); product grid renders into ul.ss__results.ss__results--grid (not ul.productGrid); pagination uses .ss__pagination__* with ?page=2 query param; sort is a custom .ss__dropdown that hash-routes (#/sort:calculated_price:asc); breadcrumbs are plain .breadcrumbs whose links (incl. the Home link) carry a.breadcrumb-label (verified live July 2 2026 — breadcrumbHome filled on plp/pdp selectors; the default .breadcrumb-label >=2 check also applies); sidebar is a single-block .page-sidebar (so the >=2-block sidebar test is skipped via sidebar:null; the category tree is covered by bestSellers #treeView); PDP has no qty stepper buttons; reviews in #yotpo-reviews-main-widget; recently-viewed SearchSpring profile is \"similar\"; Product JSON-LD is present but priceCurrency is CAD. Qty stepper absence re-verified live July 2 2026 (no button[data-action=inc/dec] in PDP HTML) — qtyIncrement/qtyDecrement stay null. Contact/quote/proClub submitUrlPatterns tightened to named Zoho forms July 2 2026 (BESTCAContactUsNew, BESTCARequestAQuote, BestAccessDoorsProClubCanadaApplication). PRO CLUB (July 14 2026): the live form gained a required country dropdown select[name=Address_Country] (options -Select- / Canada / United States, default -Select-), so hasCountry flipped false->true — the shared persona (country: Canada) now selects Canada and the address validates. The United States option is intentional (routes inattentive US applicants to a post-submit error screen linking to the US Pro Club form), NOT a region-lock deficiency, so no allowedCountries restriction is set. LIGHTHOUSE (calibrated July 2 2026, live scores homepage a11y 70 / plp 78 / pdp 68): Snap theme is structurally below a healthy a11y score, but all clear the fleet-wide accessibility:60 floor (no per-store override).thresholds.",
